  "elapsed_s": 226.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of the painting, there was a little bit left in the ceiling.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the synagogue itself apparently has gone through several transformations, the last being a kind of a folk or, or-- what is that called?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a kind of a folkloristic exhibit and cultural house at the time I was there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had an exhibit of the history of Kisvarda with very large segments of it, of course, showing the history of the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the Jewish moment was of such importance in, in the history of the city.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As best as I understand it, the, the main shul is still, at this point, some kind of a cultural institution.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "When did it stop being a synagogue?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it really stopped being a synagogue when the Germans invaded Hungary and within a matter of a few weeks after that, the persecution of the Jews that was the Holocaust, not, not the ordinary persecution which the Jews have-- of Hungary had to endure virtually from 1919 on.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would say that, curiously enough, I had a big hand in, in [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the cessation of the shul being a house of prayer and a house of God.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because on the second day of Pesach in 1944, shortly after the Germans marched into Hungary on March 19, 1944, I believe-- on that day, suddenly at the corner of, of Star and Main Street, were a line of carts appeared with gendarmes who then somehow almost immediately disappeared with Jews from the neighboring villages piled up, young and old, with a little bit of their belongings.",
      "word_count": 67
    }
  ],
